<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/193> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #193" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Caes. b.c. II 44.3" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/189> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/152> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #152" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Accused the Consuls of 474 of ignoring the agrarian law of Cassius but died in office just before the trial (Liv. 2.54.2-55.2; Dion. Hal. 9.37.1-38.3, cf. 10.38.4; Zon. 7.17)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Niccolini (FTP 13f.) would date Genucius in 474, on the ground that the new Consuls presumably took office on Sept. 1, 474, and the old ones were therefore prosecuted that autumn before the new Tribunes took office." .
